20 b. insurer of the vehicle.
21 G. 1. Where a wrecker or towing service company on a rotation
22 log seeks to dispute an action of the Department of Labor due to an
23 order regarding a complaint, the wrecker or towing service company
24 shall be provided a process by which an appeal may be made regarding
Req. No. 16927 Page 44

1 inap propriate fees charged for a service or utilization of equipment
2 related to a nonconsensual tow, or the removal of said wrecker or
3 towing service company from the rotation log.
4 2. The Department of Labor shall allow the wrecker or towing
5 service company to appeal a determination by submitting supporting
6 documentation. Once supporting documentation has been provided, the
7 Department of Labor shall make a determination of whether the
8 Department of Labor's action against the wrecker or towing service
9 company stands, or if the supporting documentation shows the
10 Department of Labor erred in its determination against the wrecker
11 or towing service company. If the Department of Labor errs
12 regarding its action against a wrecker or towing service company,
13 said company shall be entitled to collect any monies prohibited by
14 the Department of Labor.
15 H. The Department of Labor shall issue a corrective action plan
16 to any wrecker or towing service found to be in violation of the law
17 governing wrecker or towing services or deny, cancel, suspend, or
18 revoke the license of any wrecker or towing service found to be in
19 noncompliance with the law governing the wrecker or towing service.
20 K. I. Wrecker operators shall be allowed to obtain ownership
21 and insurer information, including accident reports and other public
22 records, from the Service Oklahoma Tax Commission or other states'
23 motor vehicle agencies or from law enforcement agencies for the
24 purpose of determining ownership and responsibility for wrecker
Req. No. 16927 Page 45

1 fees . In the event a state of origin is not known, the Department
2 of Public Safety and the Service Oklahoma Tax Commission shall
