24 amended to read as follows:
Req. No. 16927 Page 62

1 Section 966. A. This act shall be known and may be cited as
2 the "Nonconsensual Towing Act of 2011".
3 B. The provisions of this act shall apply to every wrecker
4 operating within the State of Oklahoma removing and storing vehicles
5 from Oklahoma roads and highways or private property as a result of
6 a nonconsensual tow.
7 C. The Corporation Commission, by Commission order, Department
8 of Labor, through the Oklahoma Wrecker and Towing Services Board,
9 shall have the power and authority necessary:
10 1. To establish wrecker rates for the transportation and
11 storage of motor vehicles removed due to a nonconsensual tow from
12 Oklahoma roads and highways or private property for any rates not
13 tied to the federal per diem rate;
14 2. To supervise and enforce such rates; and
15 3. To mediate and adjudicate complaints that may arise from
16 charges assessed as a result of such vehicle removal.
17 D. Rates as specified in Sections 953.1 and 953.2 of Title 47
18 of the Oklahoma Statutes by the Oklahoma Corporation Commission
19 shall remain in effect for twelve (12) months following the
20 effective date of this act and until rates are established by order
21 of the Commission the Board.
22 E. Rates established by the Commission Board shall be fair and
23 reasonable.
24
Req. No. 16927 Page 63

1 F. The Commission Board may assess fines or other penalties to
2 any wrecker or towing service for failure to comply with prescribed
3 rates as established by the Commission Board, failure to pay a
4 levied assessment or comply with any applicable order of the
5 Commission rule of the Board. Repeat violations by a wrecker or
6 towing service are cause for revocation of its license issued by the
7 Department of Public Safety Labor.
8 G. The Department of Public Safety shall cooperate with the
9 Commission Department of Labor to implement this act and may enter
